			<h2><a href="/blog/bedrock-custom-model-import/">Amazon Bedrock launches Custom Model Import</a></h2>
			<h3><span title="London, United Kingdom">London</span> | Published <time>23 April 2024</time> in <a href="/categories/ai">AI</a> | 10 minute read | <a href="/blog/bedrock-custom-model-import/"><img height="16" width="16" src="/img/link.svg" alt="Permalink" /></a>&nbsp;<a href="https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/machine-learning/new-capabilities-make-it-easier-to-use-amazon-bedrock-to-build-and-scale-generative-ai-applications-and-deliver-impact" target="_blank" title="Read the AWS blog post about this here"><img height="16" width="16" src="/img/box-arrow-up-right.svg" alt="London, United Kingdom" /></a></h3>
		</header>

		
		
		<p>Custom Model Import&rsquo;s = game changing! If you own your own corpus of data and are using it to train your own models, you can now bring those models to Amazon Bedrock&rsquo;s secure, managed environment.</p>
		
		<footer>
			<a href="/tags/amazonbedrock"><button>#amazonbedrock</button></a><a href="/tags/amazonwebservices"><button>#amazonwebservices</button></a><a href="/tags/aws"><button>#aws</button></a><a href="/tags/genai"><button>#genai</button></a><a href="/tags/generativeai"><button>#generativeai</button></a>
